This paper deals with text data dimension reduction and text classification, which are core topics in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel technique for dimension reduction, which is related to linear algebra and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of support vector machines (SVMs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are popular ML algorithms, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image classification as a comparison, indicating that it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) tasks such as text classification, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
